g ( unless soloing and only using DDs). just want some feedback on this topic and to see if someone has actually done significant research and has PROOF that is does/doesnt help. THANKS !!<br><br><br>nelfien/nelfie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urathji.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rathji</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Wrath</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#333333>(5/14/02 4:12:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8602.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> IMHO get your ac to 800 (the cap for casters I believe) and you HP as high as possible. Most fo the enchanters I know don't wear *any* gear specificly for cha. Although a single high cha item (like the robe from Katta +100 cha) prolly would not hurt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwtfwtfwtf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wtf Wtf Wtf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 263<br> <font color=#333333>(5/14/02 4:50:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8602.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://sux0r.jeeran.com/friend.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Enchanters and Charisma</span><hr size=1> Cha only affects charm time, not mez time. <p><img src="http://sux0r.jeeran.com/llamawalk.gif" border="0"><br><B>ICQ:151730117</B></br>Don't touch my Llamma plz</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% va